\citation{bulatov2022recurrent}
\citation{hutchins2022block}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Per-callback NLL probe by preset. Memory help (left two groups) measures how much disabling memory hurts predictions on callback vs.\ filler positions. Shuffle penalty (right two groups) measures how much substituting another sample's memory hurts vs.~the matched memory. In both groups the deeper-extraction MemRes-large preset shows a stronger ``memory cares about callbacks'' signal. The directional sign across all four bars (positive callback effect $>$ positive filler effect) is the signature of episodic, not stylistic, memory.}}{6}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:callback-bar}{{1}{6}{Per-callback NLL probe by preset. Memory help (left two groups) measures how much disabling memory hurts predictions on callback vs.\ filler positions. Shuffle penalty (right two groups) measures how much substituting another sample's memory hurts vs.~the matched memory. In both groups the deeper-extraction MemRes-large preset shows a stronger ``memory cares about callbacks'' signal. The directional sign across all four bars (positive callback effect $>$ positive filler effect) is the signature of episodic, not stylistic, memory}{figure.1}{}}
